    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-14T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-14T12:00:00-05:00" n="129"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d129">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/4471: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brussels</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-14T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 14, 1931—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 14—4:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>82. Reference is made to my telegram No. 81, July 14, 11 a.m. Although I have not
                    received any official notification, I have learned informally that at last this
                    morning the Belgian Cabinet decided to send representatives to the London
                    Conference. The delegation will leave tomorrow. An attempt is being made now to
                    follow up this decision by a notification to the Bank for International
                    Settlements of provisional postponement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
